// Interpreter fix regression guard: a mixed int-literal/float-literal
// comparison (`5 > 3.14`). Semantic analysis's common_numeric_type already
// promotes the bare int literal to F64 via an inserted Cast before this
// reaches the runtime — confirmed empirically before this fix (the runtime
// error reported "float and float", not "number and float") — so this
// exercises the same (Value::Float, Value::Float) arm the same-type
// comparisons do; no separate mixed-type arm was needed or added.
// Reference-side (interpreter) bug only — the JIT was already correct before
// this fix and should show no behavior difference here.
print(5 > 3.14)
